 {"id": "git_safety_guard-300", "title": "Implement package.json scripts extractor", "description": "## Objective

Implement an extractor for package.json files to detect executable npm script contexts.

## File Pattern

- `package.json`

## Extraction Targets

### Scripts Block (executed)
- All values in `scripts` object
- Lifecycle scripts (preinstall, postinstall, etc.)

### NOT Extracted (data only)
- `description`
- `keywords`
- `repository`
- `config` values
- Comments (JSON5 only)

## Example

```json
{
  "scripts": {
    "clean": "rm -rf dist/*",  // EXTRACT THIS
    "nuke": "rm -rf /"  // EXTRACT THIS
  },
  "description": "Uses rm -rf for cleanup"  // DO NOT extract
}
```

## Security Note

npm scripts are especially dangerous because:
- `npm install` runs lifecycle scripts automatically
- `postinstall` is a common attack vector

## Acceptance Criteria

- Correctly extracts all script values with line numbers
- Handles standard JSON format
- Ignores non-script fields
- Unit tests with representative fixtures", "notes": "## Review Additions (2026-01-08)

### False positive controls
- Extract only from executable contexts (e.g., `scripts` entries), not from:
  - package description/keywords
  - README text embedded in JSON
- Provide negative fixtures where dangerous strings appear in non-executed fields.", "status": "closed", "priority": 3, "issue_type": "task", "created_at": "2026-01-08T02:24:57.322775825Z", "created_by": "ubuntu", "updated_at": "2026-01-09T07:55:12.451434165Z", "closed_at": "2026-01-09T07:55:12.451434165Z", "close_reason": "Completed: package.json extractor implemented with 9 tests. Extracts only from scripts object, correctly ignores description/keywords/config. 676 tests pass.", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "dependencies": [{"issue_id": "git_safety_guard-300", "depends_on_id": "git_safety_guard-scan", "type": "blocks", "created_at": "2026-01-08T02:25:20.613732239Z", "created_by": "ubuntu", "metadata": "", "thread_id": ""}, {"issue_id": "git_safety_guard-300", "depends_on_id": "git_safety_guard-scan.6", "type": "parent-child", "created_at": "2026-01-08T02:45:52.357782220Z", "created_by": "ubuntu", "metadata": "", "thread_id": ""}]}
 {"id": "git_safety_guard-30oo", "title": "Command Telemetry: Statistics and summary CLI", "notes": "
---

## Additional Feature: Trend Comparison

Add comparison with previous period to show trends:

```rust
pub struct StatsTrends {
    pub commands_change: f64,      // +10% or -5%
    pub block_rate_change: f64,    // +2% or -1%
    pub top_pattern_change: Vec<(String, i32)>,  // Pattern moved up/down
}
```

## Testing Requirements

### Unit Tests

```rust
#[test]
fn test_stats_outcome_distribution() {
    let db = create_test_db_with_outcomes(70, 20, 10);  // allow, deny, warn

    let stats = db.compute_stats(30).unwrap();

    assert_eq!(stats.total_commands, 100);
    assert_eq!(stats.outcomes.allowed, 70);
    assert_eq!(stats.outcomes.blocked, 20);
    assert_eq!(stats.outcomes.warned, 10);
}

#[test]
fn test_stats_top_patterns() {
    let db = create_test_db_with_patterns(&[
        ("reset-hard", 50),
        ("force-push", 30),
        ("rm-rf", 20),
    ]);

    let stats = db.compute_stats(30).unwrap();

    assert_eq!(stats.top_patterns[0].name, "reset-hard");
    assert_eq!(stats.top_patterns[0].count, 50);
}

#[test]
fn test_stats_performance_percentiles() {
    let db = create_test_db_with_durations(&[100, 200, 300, 400, 500, 1000, 2000, 5000, 10000]);

    let stats = db.compute_stats(30).unwrap();

    assert!(stats.performance.p50 < stats.performance.p95);
    assert!(stats.performance.p95 < stats.performance.p99);
}

#[test]
fn test_stats_project_breakdown() {
    let db = create_test_db_with_projects(&[
        ("/project/a", 50),
        ("/project/b", 30),
        ("/project/c", 20),
    ]);

    let stats = db.compute_stats(30).unwrap();

    assert_eq!(stats.top_projects[0].path, "/project/a");
    assert_eq!(stats.top_projects[0].command_count, 50);
}

#[test]
fn test_stats_agent_distribution() {
    let db = create_test_db_with_agents(&[
        ("claude_code", 60),
        ("codex", 30),
        ("gemini", 10),
    ]);

    let stats = db.compute_stats(30).unwrap();

    assert_eq!(stats.agents[0].name, "claude_code");
    assert_eq!(stats.agents[0].count, 60);
}

#[test]
fn test_stats_with_trends() {
    // Create data spanning two periods
    let db = create_test_db_with_trend_data();

    let stats = db.compute_stats_with_trends(30).unwrap();

    assert!(stats.trends.is_some());
    let trends = stats.trends.unwrap();
    // Should show change percentage
    assert!(!trends.commands_change.is_nan());
}

#[test]
fn test_stats_empty_db() {
    let db = TelemetryDb::open_in_memory().unwrap();

    let stats = db.compute_stats(30).unwrap();

    assert_eq!(stats.total_commands, 0);
    assert!(stats.outcomes.allowed == 0);
}

#[test]
fn test_stats_json_output() {
    let db = create_test_db_with_data(100);

    let stats = db.compute_stats(30).unwrap();
    let json = serde_json::to_string(&stats).unwrap();

    let parsed: serde_json::Value = serde_json::from_str(&json).unwrap();
    assert!(parsed["total_commands"].is_number());
}
```

